 Novomiwr. you\ncan voice your convictions whit-h\nwill have crystallized between now\nanti then. But the privacy ot\u2018 tin\npoll is not yours unless you hovel\nregistered. So do it now!\nARTHI'R L. HAYES\nTACOMA\u2014Through the untir\ning efforts of Hon. Harry I\u2019. (\u2018:lin,\nMayor, and Dr. It. Farghur, ili\nrector of Health, Tacoma citizens\nhave been provided with the fol~\nlowing services and careful con\n}sideratlon should be given by all.\ni Service Committee Needs Help\nThe Service Committee of the\nl'llblll! Health Nursing Assm-iu\ntion is offering an opportunity to\nthe women of the community to\nrender a servive at clinics and in\nthe office. it\" you know anyone\ninterested in helping cull MA.\n2636 leaving home and address.\nSuch assistance is urgently\nneeded. according to Miss Grace\nCoffman. supervisor of nurses\nin the Tacoma Department of\nPublic Health.\nAt the clinics the assistants will\nreceive the patients, weigh and\u2018\nmeasure babies, and file x-rays.;\nBesides the clinic work there isi\nsewing to he done in making up\nrons. and mending; nurses bags\nto be supplied (refilled with fold-i\ned soft tissues. rolled cord dress\u2014i\nings. fresh folded towels. etc.)\u2018\nand clerical'assistance for the\nstaff nurses in the officer\nTwo lectures are being planned\nfor the women expecting to par\nticipate so that they may become\nmore familiar with the services\n2.: Stop folks Talking About Your\nm\n{a\ng\nU.\u2018 /2 I Yes people will talk about your gray, drab hair\ng I l about how much older you look how much\nprettier you used to be. Don't let gray hair rob\n[jg/w you of the pleasures of youthful looks and pop\nf by ulurity. Put rich, natural looking, beautiful color\ninto your hair with Lariense.\nI[y y 9'\nHAVE IEAUTIFUHY (DIORED NATURM [OOKING \u201cAll\nit i\nj 9:. 2 Color Your\na Hair This\nI V.) Easy Way\nTo give your hair new, rich, natu\njg;- ral looking color (black, brown.\n\u2018.\u2018z- blonde) start using Godefroy's\ni Larieuse liair Coloring NOW .I. I\ng 9; acts quic l oes on even y\n\u2014won't rug offer wash out\u2014\nunaffected [2' heat\u2014permits per-\nE 3 manents an stylish hairdos\n2. known and used for 45 years. Your\n7\u2019 dealer will give your money baCk \\e'\n5E if you're not 100% satis\ufb01e\n3... \u201dmm, SHAMPOO with labor. V\n55. W Hon Applvlno\n1; l-hvu Halt Coloring.\n\u2019:\u2018\u00e9\u2018a\u00e9\u2019www\u2018\ufb02o A\n\u201911\"\neonsrnov's\ni' 0\n2c :2 We\nac HAIR colonmc.\n'v.\u2018 CAUTION: Uso Only at Directed on label.\n3 LIII -ll no! .25. 25 l\n.2-\u2018-. \"\u201dm \u201c\u201c\u2018mb\u2018lfc\u2018. li'llullhl 533... nun-u fiil\u2018lo'.\u2018 \u201c1' \u201cmm\nMil???\u201c\n\u2019y\u2018k CENTRAL\nW 9? my\u201d 1\" LOCATION\nI 1 1 a\n)'_ Convenience to both\nthe family and those\namending {unerals in a\nFirst Consideration\u2014tho\nColonial Mortuary is ideally\n9x situaied Io serve.\n_ \u201cSo Much in Service\u2014So Little in Cost\"\nB MOI. M A N L U \u2018l\u2019 Z\nEAST I4\"! SANDY BLVD.\nwonm w.. cunwnt \"In\ufb02uence\n\"widen! E\u00c5ST'4III\n3\noi the lieparunent vi Public\nHealth. The first meeting will be\non Wednesday, March 27, 1946.\nat 1: p. m. in room 103 of the\n(\u2018ity Hall .\\\u2018nnex This will be\n_ followed by another session on\nApril it). 1946. at the some time\nand place.\nFor years, the Pierce County\ngroup have been leaders in the\n_ promotion of health and prepay\nment for medical care, having or\u2019\nganized the Pierce County indus\ntrial Medical Bureau in 1917.\n'i\u2018ht- essentials of the national\nprogram entail briefly:\nThe American Medical Associa\ntion urges a minimum standard of\nnutrition. housing. clothing and\nrecreation as fundamental to good\nhealth and as an objective to be\nachieved in any suitable health\nprogram. The responsibility for\nattainment of this standard should\nbe placed as far as possible on\nthe individual, but the application\nof community effort. compatible\nwith the maintenance of free en\nterprise. should bu encouraged\nwith governmental aid where\nneeded.\nThe provision of preventive\nmedical services through profes\nsionally competent health depart\u2014\nments with sufficient staff and\nequipment to meet community\nneeds is recognized as essential\nin a health program. The prln~\nciple oi\u2019 tederal aid through pro\nvision oI funds. or personnel is\nrecognized with the understand\ning that local areas shall control\ntheir own agencies as has been\nestablished in the field of educa\ntion. lleaith departments should\nnot assume the care of the sick\nas a function. Medical care to\n\u2018those unable to provide for them\n\u2018selves is best administered by lo\ncal and private agencies with the\naid of public funds when needed.\nThe procedures established by\nmodern medicine for advice to the\nprospective mother and for ade\nquate. care in childbirth should\nbe made available to all at a\nprice that they can afford to pay.\nWhen local funds are lacking for\nthe care of those unable to pay,\nfederal aid should be supplied\nwith the funds administered thru\nlocal or state agencies.\nThe child should have through\nout infancy proper attention. in\ncluding scientific nutrition, im\nmunization against preventable\ndisease and other services includ~\ned in infant welfare. such serv\nices are best supplied by person\nal contact between the mother\nand the individual physician but\nmay be provided through child\ncare and infant welfare stations\nadministered under local auspices\nwith support by tax funds when\never the need can be shown.\nThe best work is not done for\na. price, but by mon whose pride\nwml\u2019tt let them do inferior work.","height":"28544","width":"21492"}}
